[1] China (Sichuan)
Date: Tue 21 Feb 2107 15:36 PM CST
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19088.html

Wusheng county of Guangan city [Sichuan province] reported 2 human H7N9 AIV [influenza A(H7N9)] cases (one fatal) on [20 Feb 2017] after the confirmation from Sichuan provincial CDC. The epidemiological investigation revealed both patients had a history of exposure to live poultry, but no epidemiological connection with each other. The environmental surveillance conducted by Guangan city CDC showed a chicken anal swab sample tested positive for H7 AIV, proving H7 AIV existed in the local environment (market). The 92 close contacts of the patients are under medical monitoring, no ILI [influenza-like illness] symptoms has been reported so far.

Sichuan province has reported 8 cases of human H7N9 AIV so far, 5 cases in Suining city (one fatal), one case in Deyang city, and 2 cases in Guangan (one fatal)

