[In view of the WHO's update of 20 Feb 2017 and the high number of fatal cases seen among A/H7N9 positive cases, active surveillance is required, as well as investigation into the viral spread and whether some changes in genome may be enhancing its potential to infect humans. - Mod.UBA]
